Besides the <a2_0><b6_0>absence of vowel reduction<b6_0/><a2_0/>, some dialects have <b7_0>high or diphthongal /e~i̯ɛ/<b7_0/> in the place of Proto-Slavic *ě and /o~u̯ɔ/ in stressed closed syllables (as in Ukrainian) instead of Standard Russian /e/ and /o/.
